job_title: Certified Medical Assistant in Honolulu, HI
pros:
Flexibility, PTO, Medical, Dental and Vision. My "team"  worked well together. We are like an Ohana. 

There is Pediatrics,  Women's Health, Dental, Behavioral Health and Adult Medicine. Also, Social Service. 

Non profit medical center which caters to people on Medicaid or no insurance. They have helped alot of individuals with their health needs.
cons:
Unappreciated for the hard work you do. I understand non profit and low pay go hand and hand. But for someone to work there for 3 years and not get a penny raise and recognition for how many duties you perform, is why there is a high turnover.  Recognition goes a long way with low pay, but when you have no recognition AND low pay.. 
I'm on my way out the door...
